<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbbc1bbc0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s2000e–11"><num value="2000e–11">§ 2000e–11.</num><heading> Veterans’ special rights or preference</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing contained in this subchapter shall be construed to repeal or modify any Federal, State, territorial, or local law creating special rights or preference for veterans.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbbc1bbc1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/88/352/tVII/s712">Pub. L. 88–352, title VII, § 712</ref>, <date date="1964-07-02">July 2, 1964</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/78/265">78 Stat. 265</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
